# Seiton Brain

Personal AI assistant: Telegram input (text/voice) → structured Obsidian vault notes.
Learning project + real utility. Name from **Seiton** (整頓) — put everything in its place.

## Flow

```
Telegram → POST /webhook (X-Telegram-Bot-Api-Secret-Token)
         → immediate 200 + "Wird verarbeitet…"
         → Celery worker: [Whisper if voice] → OpenAI classify → Postgres → .md in vault
         → Telegram: "Gespeichert als [[Title]] unter Folder"
```

## Stack

FastAPI · PostgreSQL + SQLAlchemy (async) + Alembic · Celery + Redis · OpenAI (LLM + Whisper) · Docker Compose · Obsidian vault (local mount)

## Structure

- `app/telegram/` — webhook, send_message, download_file
- `app/worker/` — Celery tasks (`process_text_message`, `process_voice_message`)
- `app/llm/` — provider interface, OpenAI, `ClassificationResult` (category, title, summary, related)
- `app/vault/` — reader (existing notes for context), writer (Markdown + `[[links]]`)
- `app/transcription/` — Whisper API
- `app/models/` — `Entry` table
- `prompts/classify.txt` — versioned LLM prompt (not inline in code)

Vault folders: School, Work, Private, Ideas, Travel, Notes (`vault.example/` is template; personal vault is gitignored at `/vault/`).

## Status (v0.2.0 — Phase A+B done)

Core pipeline works: text + voice, async workers with retries, DB persistence, append/create logic, structured tags, Telegram slash commands (`/recent`, `/find`, `/undo`), atomic vault writes, allowlist + idempotency, 117 tests + GitHub CI. Phase C next (self-hosting, REST API, logging).

